content:
Create an Article .zip File for Import

To complete your article import, create a .zip file with your parameters, .csv, and .html files, and upload them to Salesforce Knowledge.

Required user permissions:

Manage Salesforce Knowledge
Manage Articles
Manage Knowledge Article Import/Export
Read, Create, Edit, and Delete on the article type

Create a .zip file containing:
The .csv file.
The folder containing the .html files to import.
The folder containing the image files referenced in the .html files.
The .properties file.

Important requirements for the .zip file:

There can only be one .csv file and one .properties file.
The .csv file and the .properties file must be in the root directory.
Preserve the folder and subfolder structure during compression.
Do not use special characters in the .zip file name.
The .zip file cannot exceed 20 MB or have individual, uncompressed files exceeding 10 MB.
.csv files can only contain up to 9,999 articles and translations.
.csv rows can only contain up to 400,000 characters.
.csv cells can only contain up to 32 KB of data.
Each article in the .csv file can only have up to 49 translations.

From Setup, search for Import Articles, then select it. 
In Lightning Knowledge, select Knowledge Base from the dropdown.
Select the appropriate article type for the imported articles in Salesforce Classic.
Click Browse to select the .zip file and click OK.
If your import contains translations, select Contains translations?.
Click Import Now.

Check the status of your import on the Article Imports page.
title: Creating a .zip File for Article Import in Service Cloud
